The UN Chief again called on all parties, including the divided UN Security Council, to unite and support negotiations to find a political solution.
Ban said Wednesday at a conference that he intends to meet this month with foreign ministers from five permanent countries present at the Council - USA, Russia, China, England and France - on the sidelines of the General Assembly's ministerial session to discuss Syria.
Ban expressed regret that the divisions in the Council and between the Syrian people and the regional powers "made this situation unresolved".
Ban asked the five permanent members to show the solidarity and unity shown when they were able to conclude an agreement on Iran's nuclear weapons, thus addressing the crisis in Syria.
