In fact, a single meeting attended by 12 people led to the development of a multi-criteria (MCDA) model of decision analysis to summarise their views on the negative effects associated with different nicotine-containing products; the results of this meeting were briefly presented in a research paper.
McKee and Capewell either claimed that one of the sponsors of the meeting was a company called EuroSwiss Health, whose executive director was said to have previously received funding from British American Tobacco for an independent study.
