The moment that put Nick at the top of his head was when, after a minor accident, when he had been hit by another car, he discovered that he had an alcoholemia three times over the legal limit, although one evening before he had only consumed one beer.
After years of uncounted investigations, it was discovered that Nick suffered from an extremely rare disease, "Auto-brewery syndromes".
Basically, the body causes all carbohydrates consumed to ferment, turning into alcohol.
