The government approved, on Wednesday, the "National Strategy on Immigration 2015-2018" and the "Action Plan for the current year", documents considered to be "an additional stage Romania is going through in its efforts to modernise the process of managing immigration in the national territory", according to a press release.
The source cited shows that the strategy aims to effectively manage the phenomenon of immigration, including general strategic objectives, specific objectives and guidelines for action reflecting policies set at European level, adapted to national realities.
In view of the problems faced by states in the immediate vicinity of Romania, measures are being taken to manage the unitary and coherent situation resulting from the possible influx of illegal immigrants into the territory of Romania caused by situations of political, social, economic or military crisis.
"The Roman authorities will contribute to the creation of a flexible admission system, but at the same time they will pay special attention to citizens from states with potential migrationist or which may affect national security," adds the recalled source.
The strategy identifies a number of factors that can influence immigration and asylum, including maintaining the conflict situation in Syria, reactivating the conflict in Iraq, maintaining an unstable situation in the border areas of Romania (Ukraine, Transnistria), perpetuating and increasing the intensity of the Israeli-Palestinian armed conflict.
On the other hand, the document also sets out a number of general strategic objectives related to immigration, such as: promoting legal migration, stricter controls on the legality of the residence of third-country nationals on the territory of Romania and the proper application of remoteness and restrictive measures, and improving the national asylum system.
The national strategy shall also include specific objectives relevant to the transposition and implementation of the overall strategic objectives.
These include: facilitating access to the territory of Romania by third-party citizens who respond to the needs of employment of the labour force, promoting access by third-party citizens to higher education institutions in Romania for the areas and professions identified as deficits.
With regard to the 2015 Action Plan, the Government appreciates that it represents "a means by which concrete activities are established that lead to the creation of a flexible system to stop the growing phenomenon of migration".
