What is the connection between Osama bin Laden and the collapse of the Mecca crane?
Saudi authorities have announced that the Saudi giant Binladin Group, belonging to the family of Osama bin Laden, is "partially responsible" for the collapse of a crane, on Friday, on the Great Mosque of Mecca, accident after which 107 people died.
