What button will appear soon
Millions of Facebook users have become accustomed to the "Like" button, and now the representatives of the social network are preparing another opposite, the "Dislike".
Marti, Mark Zuckerberg, co-founder and executive director of the company, announced on the account that this button will be available soon, informs New York Times on the blog.
Zuckerberg said the "Dislike" button would rather show a shade of what a user feels than a simple option.
However, his announcement raised the issue that Facebook might become a less friendly place.
Zuckerberg said he wants to avoid the moments when someone posts on the account or an important event in life, and someone else will give "Dislike".
The users of the network, which has reached 1.5 billion active accounts, have long requested the opportunity to express their negative emotions or empathy with something sad.
Mark Zuckerberg also said that it is not very comfortable for people to give "Like" to current events, such as the refugee crisis, or in the event of a death of a family member.
"You may not feel comfortable giving Like to that post," said Facebook representative.
The option of a new Facebook button was not welcomed by everyone.
"There's already enough hate on Facebook and social networks," Atiq Haneef said in Afghanistan, on the Facebook page of the New York Times, where the article on this topic was posted.
"I'll give 'Dislike' to the 'Dislike' button," he said.
Roger Anderson, a microbiologist from Atlanta, argued that there is nothing wrong with this button, encouraging people to have different opinions on Facebook.
Debra Aho Williamson, social media analyst at eMarketer, said it's hard to imagine that a single button can transmit a complex range of negative emotions.
Moreover, she claims, the campaign is approaching in America, and the "Dislike" button would create a total disaster.
