The CJ decision to discontinue direct negotiations was challenged in court by Impex Romcatel.
The outgoing Court sent the complaint to the CNSC, which rejected it as late.
This does not mean, however, that CJ can start looking for another designer.
Impex Romcatel has the possibility to attack the CNSC decision in the Court of Appeal, only after a final sentence of it being able to take into account the finding of another designer.
Thus, work on building consolidation could be resumed as soon as possible next year.
Our intention is to resume work as soon as possible.
In principle, the refurbishment of the technical project should not take long, but we must reach the conclusion of a contract.
"We're waiting to see if the CNSC decision will be attacked or not," Timofciuc said.
The consolidation work of the former police headquarters began in 2011.
A first contract of employment was terminated in April 2012, after work of 4.5 million lei had been carried out.
The auction was resumed and the contract was awarded by Moldoconstruct SA.
However, the firm went into insolvency, and this contract was terminated, after payments of 1.5 million lei had been made.
The work has so far been carried out in a proportion of about 50%.
Initially, work on consolidation, recasting and attenuation of the building had been estimated at 7.7 million lei.
